        <h1 class="program_title">List program</h1>

        <p>This year, the BDS has worked hard to diversify the
            range of sports on offer so that everyone can fi nd something
            to enjoy at Télécom Paris. It offers a wide variety of weekly
            activities, regular participation in tournaments in different
            sports and access to sporting events at reduced prices. We
            are committed to maintaining this ambition by continuing
            to work on current projects (the issue of compulsory sport,
            extension of the Ekiden to the Ile de France region, etc.) to
            make Télécom Paris a school that is recognized for its sports.</p>

        <p>Developing sports for all is one of our priorities for next
            year. Including international students in sports activities
            seems essential to us. This is why it will be important, for
            example, to communicate in French and English. The
            current BDS would like to have two leaders per sport next
            year. One of them could be responsible for the inclusion of
            internationals during weekly training sessions, for example
            by making sure that they understand the instructions given
            by the coaches.</p>

        <p>Sport for all also requires equitable access to sport.
            Women’s sports are under-resourced in some disciplines.
            
            We plan to bring together the schools on the plateau to set
            up joint teams. The arrival of AgroParisTech on the Plateau
            may play a determining role in this project. With the other
            schools on the Plateau (SupOptique, Ensta, ENSAE, etc.), we
            will be able to form new women’s teams.</p>


        <p>This opening up to other schools will lead to the
            emergence of new teams in new sports for which the
            number of players is limited at Télécom, whether for men’s
            or women’s sports.</p>


        <p>We are also keen to offer the practice of new sports to
            Télécommians. We will work on the creation of a ski club and
            the addition of disciplines such as crossfi t and petanque.
            Concerning the discovery of sports at the beginning of the
            year, we would like to extend the period of discovery of the
            sports offered at Télécom and repeat it a little later in the
            year. This will allow all students to better integrate into the
            sports life, even if they did not have the opportunity to do so
            in September.</p>


            <p>The inter-school League of Legends tournament
                organized by Télécom also shows that e-sport is a fully
                integrated discipline. We must continue to develop e-sports
                events that contribute to the infl uence of Télécom on the
                Plateau.</p>


            <p>More generally, maintaining stronger relations with the
                BDS of IP Paris in order to reinforce visibility on the events
                organized by Télécom Paris would be very effective. The
                drastic increase in the number of registrations for the Ekiden
                this year following contact with the BDS of the Plateau is
                proof of this. This project was a great success and shows the
                capacity of the BDS to organize large-scale sports events.
                Our ambition is to extend the Ekiden to all the schools in
                the Ile de France.</p>


            <p>This inter BDS connection is a fi rst step in the
                improvement of the communication of the sports events of
                the plateau. It is an avenue that we must continue to explore.
                For example, the IP Fusion tournament lacked visibility, even
                though it was an important event that Télécom SudParis
                organized (multisport tournament and evening) and for
                which they made the effort to travel. Including the other
                BDS of the Plateau in this project leaves great room for
                improvement.</p>

            

            <p>We also feel it is important to strengthen the
                communication of the BDS within the school, starting with
                the refurbishment of the association’s website. We will also
                set up a calendar accessible to all to reference upcoming
                sports events.</p>



            <p>The WER, the WEI Olympics and the Ekiden are all
                events that we could put on this calendar and that we would
                of course like to maintain in the years to come. We will
                propose fun sports activities to Telecommians to present
                sports in a different way through specifi c outings. We will
                submit to other associations ideas for activities such as a
                charity race for TeleSpoir, a timed garbage collection with
                MAD, or a Tea Mile with Thé Lait Com.</p>



            <p>Finally, in order to avoid too much compartmentalization
                between sports, we will organize fun sports outings outside
                Telecom (Paintball; Trampoline Park; District 78...).</p>


            <p> We will also continue the efforts of the current BDS
                to try to insert sports into the academic curriculum of
                the Telecommians. We will propose to the administration
                different possibilities to recognize the regular practice of at
                least one sport.</p>


            <p>Quality sports equipment is necessary for the
                development of sport. It seems important to us to set up
                a rigorous management of the BDS equipment to avoid as
                much as possible the degradation and the loss of equipment.
                This will involve a complete inventory of the equipment,
                a reorganization of the premises to make
                frequently used equipment more accessible,
                and a loan system that is both accessible and
                
                supervised to allow Telecommians to remove the fi nancial
                obstacle to the discovery of sports. We will negotiate with
                other associations to provide additional storage space for
                seldom used equipment.</p>



            <p>The BDS already has key partnerships, the most
                important being the Société Générale. We aspire to establish
                partnerships with sports retailers to offer equipment at
                discounted prices. This would allow the BDS to maintain an
                adequate supply of quality equipment, and to offer discounts
                to Telecommians for their personal purchases.</p>


            <p>It is also important to preserve and expand our access to
                the sports facilities of the plateau, for example by proposing
                a pooling of weight training slots.</p>


            <p>In addition, we want to increase the fi nancial support of
                the BDS in order to allow the most motivated Telecommians
                to participate in high level competitions. We would also like
                to continue offering tickets to sporting events at a reduced
                price.</p>


                
               



